;Draft notes
*Detroit's second-round pick will go to the Nashville Predators, as the result of a trade on March 5, 2014, that sent [[David Legwand]] to Detroit, in exchange for [[Patrick Eaves]], [[Calle Järnkrok|Calle Jarnkrok]], and this pick (being conditional at the time of the trade).<ref>{{cite news|title=Predators trade pending free agent David Legwand to Red Wings|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/sports/hockey/predators-trade-pending-free-agent-david-legwand-to-red-wings/article17334682/|date=March 5, 2014|accessdate=May 19, 2014|work=The Globe and Mail}}</ref> The condition – Nashville will receive a second-round pick in 2014 if Detroit qualifies for the [[2014 Stanley Cup playoffs]] – was converted on April 9, 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Wings secure 23rd straight playoff spot|url=http://redwings.nhl.com/club/news.htm?id=713754|date=April 9, 2014|accessdate=May 19, 2014}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note1|a|a}}San Jose's seventh-round pick will go to Detroit, as the result of a trade on June 10, 2012, that sent [[Brad Stuart]] to San Jose, in exchange for [[Andrew Murray (ice hockey)|Andrew Murray]] and this pick (being conditional at the time of the trade).<ref name="StuartSharks">{{cite news|last=St. James|first=Helene|title=Red Wings trade Brad Stuart to San Jose for Andrew Murray, draft pick|url=http://www.freep.com/article/20120610/SPORTS05/120610016/Red-Wings-trade-Brad-Stuart-to-San-Jose-for-Andrew-Murray-draft-pick|accessdate=May 19, 2014|newspaper=[[Detroit Free Press]]|date=June 10, 2012}}</ref> The condition – Stuart is re-signed by San Jose for the 2012–13 season – was converted on June 18, 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sharks ink D Stuart to three-year, $10.8 million deal|url=https://www.tsn.ca/nhl/story/?id=398651|accessdate=May 19, 2014|newspaper=[[Total Sports Network]]|date=June 18, 2012}}</ref>

